<HL>
   Logicon to Buy Hadson Unit
</HL>
<DATE>
08/16/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   LGN HAD
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   LOS ANGELES -- Logicon Inc. said it agreed in principle to
acquire the Ultrasystems Defense Inc. subsidiary of Oklahoma
City-based Hadson Corp.
   Terms weren't disclosed. Ultrasystems Defense, an Irvine,
Calif.-based professional services company specializing in
systems engineering and software development, has annual
revenue of about $27 million and employs 280 people. Logicon
provides advanced technology systems and services to support
national security, civil and industrial needs.
